<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
The present genus was created in 1953 with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Allonothrus" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuilingi">A. schuilingi</taxonomicName>
as type and single representative. Later (Van der Hammen, 1955a) I studied the development of the type-species and classified it with the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trhypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyriformis">Angelia pyriformis Berlese</taxonomicName>
does not belong to the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
(the notogaster is unideficient; phi1 + d of tibia I is long, etc.), but it appears to be related to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Allonothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Allonothrus</taxonomicName>
schuilingi, so that it is preliminary regarded here as a representative of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
